The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, August 22, 2004 				Metro Recommends
THE VCD 
	(MusicWorld, Rs 299) Three friends drift apart after a tragedy only to be rejoined by a brutal incident years later. Sean Penns sensitive performance fetched him the Academy Award for best actor this year in this brilliant thriller directed by Clint Eastwood. THE EVENT
	(The Oberoi Grand, August 28) Catch some of the countrys top models  Nina Manuel, Fleur Xavier and Jyoti Brahmin  strutting some of the best ensembles designed by the graduating students of NiFD. Fashion designer Wendell Rodericks will be chief judge at the show themed around urban, techno and eco-friendly lifestyles. THE TOURNEY				 																																	(Space Circle, from 9 am, August 22) Tendulkar may be out of the Holland Cup with a tennis elbow, but closer home you can catch Sachin clones sweating it out in the air-conditioned comfort of the VIP Road club. The 3rd Corporate amp; Club Indoor Cricket Tournament presented by The Telegraph with rules for every run and loads of fun. 

